President Trump held a press conference in the Roosevelt Room to discuss the signing of the new U.S.-Japan Trade Agreement and the U.S.-Japan Digital Trade Agreement. He thanked Prime Minister Abe of Japan for his partnership and highlighted the benefits of the trade deals, including job creation, increased investment and commerce, and reduced trade deficits. The agreements will provide enhanced access to the Japanese market for American farmers and ranchers. The President also addressed the ongoing trade negotiations with China, expressing optimism for a deal but warning of consequences if China does not comply. He touched on the situation in Hong Kong, expressing hope for a peaceful resolution, and defended his decision to withdraw troops from Syria, emphasizing that the U.S. cannot stay there forever. He also commented on the impeachment inquiry, calling it a "scam" and accusing the Democrats of defrauding the American people.